<br>
Basic premise.  I don't mind posting to a board tarring and feathering someone who has really screwed up.  Posts that expose the cheats and lowlifes of our friendly little server are fine with me.  But making a &quot;Master List&quot; and giving any person or people the power to add to it officially is just going way too far.  Details and reasoning get lost.<br>
<br>
Let's just say, hypothetically, I was someone responsible for that list.  Now I've got real losers on the list like Atuma and Valancer, and no one would disagree for a moment they deserve the brutal reputations they've earned.  Then I take someone who's done something borderline, but really cheesed me off, and I put him on the same list.  Merely by association with names like Valancer and Atuma I can severly screw that person's reputation.  But what has that person actually done?  Maybe he's done something you would think is really scummy.  Maybe I think that but you would disagree with me and, given the chance to look at that situation alone, you would say &quot;Well, maybe that was just a misunderstanding....&quot;<br>
<br>
In short, you want to post about some specific loser, on a specific thread, I'm all for that, and may each individual issue receieve however much attention it duely deserves.  But a &quot;Master&quot; blacklist is a very bad idea.   I wouldn't trust even Captian Roleplay with that responsibility, and that's saying a lot.  Along with &quot;RP Nazis&quot; we'd end up with &quot;FV McCarthys&quot; and that's just bad.<br>
<br>
Valquiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usydiafv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sydia FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 104<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/9/02 8:48:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1173.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Badass list names...</span><hr size=1> add Sydia, i hear she's completely evil, wholly intolerable...based on everything i've heard she should be black listed and shunned by the entire server because someone said they disliked her, or had bad experiences with her.  i am all for this black list idea, as it keeps me from having to talk to and discover peoples true colors for myself, and prevents me from forming my own opinions altogether.  What a great idea!<br>
