<br>
personally, i made a post on this board asking apep for a particular forum, not a &quot;Master List&quot;, but a forum where people could put their accusations and actually carry it out court-style, almost like it's been happening here in the Soapbox already.  of course, this suggestion was stricken down because of it's &quot;potential for abuse&quot;.  that potential is always there, but i think it's more of a probability in the Soapbox where people take off the gloves anyway.<br>
<br>
it's almost bordering on hypocrisy to state that blacklists or court-forums aren't going to be allowed, and then allow every other post to accuse someone new on this board.  just peruse the titles of the most recent few pages of the Soapbox.  practically every other discussion these days is in reference to 'soandso, who cheated suchandsuch'.  <br>
<br>
these posts have been enlightening.  yes, i agree that perhaps no one should be given a final authority on one single master list, but what is wrong with just a separate forum for these things which are being posted anyway?<br>
<br>
at least, if someone had been accused sometime in the past and it had just come to their attention, they'd know where to look.  word would get out, and folks would learn of it.  besides, i'm not really sure what the Soapbox was designed for (general bitching, i'm assuming) but holding court was probably not one of its original purposes.  <br>
<br>
who knows...<br>
